Post._content:
# Centos
## 
- nethogs   ``
- screen    ``
- lrzsz     ``
- htop      ``

---

## 
1. vim /etc/profile
2. 
``` shell
export LC_ALL="zh_CN.UTF-8"  
export LANG="zh_CN.UTF-8"
```
3. source /etc/profile 
4. echo $LANG 

---

## gcc,g++
```
yum  install python34-devel
yum  install python-devel
```

---

## python3.4pip3.4
1. epel
```
    yum install epel-release
```
2. Python3.4
```
    yum install python34
```
3. pip3
```
    yum install python34-setuptools
    easy_install-3.4 -i https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple pip
```
4. pip3,
```
    pip3 install requests
```
5. pip  
Linux ~/.pip/pip.conf () 
``` shell
    [global]  
    index-url = https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple
```
---

## mono
```
rpm --import "http://keyserver.ubuntu.com/pks/lookup?op=get&search=0x3FA7E0328081BFF6A14DA29AA6A19B38D3D831EF"    
yum-config-manager --add-repo http://download.mono-project.com/repo/centos/  yum -y install yum-utils
yum -y install mono-complete
```

---

## jdk
1. 
```
    rpm -ivh jdk.rpm
```
2. 
```
vim /etc/profile
```
    
```
  export JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/jdk1.8.0_131
  CLASSPATH=.:$JAVA_HOME/lib/dt.jar:$JAVA_HOME/lib/tools.jar:$JRE_HOME/lib
  export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH
  source /etc/profile
```

Post.title: ArchLinux
Post._content:
# arch
## 
1. fdisk mkfs.ext4
2. 
```
ping -c 4 http://www.baidu.com
```
3. 
```
cd /etc/pacman.d
sed -i "s/^\b/#/g" mirrorlist 
vim mirrorlist
163#
```
4. 
```
pacman -Syy
pacstrap /mnt base base-devel
genfstab -U -p /mnt >>/mnt/etc/fstab
arch-chroot /mnt /bin/bash
```
5. 
    ```
    vim /etc/locale.gen
    ```
    - 
    ```
    en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8
    zh_CN.UTF-8 UTF-8
    zh_TW.UTF-8 UTF-8
    ```
    - 
    ```
    locale-gen
    echo LANG=en_US.UTF-8 > /etc/locale.conf
    ln -s /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Shanghai /etc/localtime
    hwclock --systohc --utc
    ```
6. 
```
echo archlinuxpc > /etc/hostname
```
7. 
```
systemctl start dhcpcd
systemctl enable dhcpcd
```
8. ,
    - root 
    ```
        passwd 
    ```
    - 
    ```
    useradd -m -g users -G wheel -s /bin/bash 
    passwd 
    ```
    - sudo
    ```
    vim /etc/sudoers
    ```
9. 
    - UEFI:
    ```
    mkdir -p /mnt/boot/EFI  (UEFI)
    mount /dev/sdX(Y) /mnt/boot/efi  (UEFI)
    pacman -S dosfstools efibootmgr
    pacman -S grub
    pacman -S os-prober
    grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot/efi --bootloader-id=arch_grub --recheck
    grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
    ```
    - bios
    ```
    pacman -S grub
    grub-install /dev/sda --force
    grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
    ```
8. 
    - wifi
    ```
    pacman -S dialog  (wifi-menu)
    exit
    pacman -S dialog
    umount /mnt/{home,boot} 
    umount /mnt 
    reboot
    ```
9. 
    - 
    ```
    pacman -S alsa-utils
    alsamixer #
    ```
    - intel
    ```
    pacman -S mesa xf86-video-intel
    ```
    - 
    ```
    pacman -S xf86-input-synaptics
    pacman -S xorg xorg-server xorg-xinit xorg-utils xorg-server-utils
    ```
10. 
    - 
    ```
    pacman -S fcitx fcitx-qt unrar p7zip cpio zip unzip leafpad xarchiver firefox firefox-i18n-zh-cn flashplugin
    ```
    - 
    ```
    pacman -S ttf-dejavu wqy-zenhei wqy-microhei
    ```
    - gnome
    ``` 
    pacman -S gdm gnome gnome-extra
    systemctl enable gdm
    ```
    - ntfs
    ``` 
    sudo pacman -S ntfs-3g
    ```
    - 
    ```
    systemctl enable NetworkManager
    ```
    - wifi
    ``` 
    sudo pacman -S dnsmasq
    ```
11. 
    - 
    ```
    vim ~/.profile
    ```
    
    ```
    export XIM=fcitx
    export XMODIFIERS="@im=fcitx"
    export GTK_IM_MODULE=fcitx
    export QT_IM_MODULE=fcitx
    export XIM_PROGRAM=fcitx
    fcitx &
    ```
    - 
    ```
    vim /usr/share/polkit-1/actions/org.freedesktop.udisks2.policy
    ```
    id="org.freedesktop.udisks2.filesystem-mount-system"
    <allow_active>auth_admin_keep</allow_active><allow_active>yes</allow_active>
